.DS_Store
# Populated secret seed files (see scripts/seed-secrets.sh + secrets.template.json).
# `secrets.template.json` itself IS committed — it's the shape doc.
#
# The intended convention is `marshal-secrets.{env}.json` at the repo root or
# under marshal/. Extra patterns below catch common "I just named it whatever"
# cases — belt-and-braces so a wrong-named seed file can't be accidentally
# pulled into a `git add -A` commit. Add new patterns here, don't narrow these.
marshal-secrets.*.json
marshal-secrets*.json
*-secrets.json
*-creds.json
*-tokens.json
# One-off seed-file names, root-anchored so they only guard the repo root and
# can't collide with chart assets deeper in the tree (e.g.
# chart/dashboards/marshal.json). The documented convention is
# marshal-secrets.{env}.json; these are belt-and-braces.
/secrets.json
/creds.json
